openCall.name: openCall
openCall.organization: Hewlett Packard Company, OpenCall Business Unit
openCall.description: This is the MIB module that describes an HP private mib for the management of OpenCall traps.

sourcePlatformEntity.name: sourcePlatformEntity
sourcePlatformEntity.description: This is the source entity that sends the trap, typically this is a combination of platform and machine name. (ex: oc_platform, nta2225.india.hp.com

sourceObjectID.name: sourceObjectID
sourceObjectID.description: This identifies the objectID of the instance that sends the trap. (ex: Process Name)

perceveidSeverity.name: perceveidSeverity
perceveidSeverity.description: This identifies the severity of the trap. Possible severity are 1. Major 2. Minor 3. Warning 4. Informative 5. Critical

alarmText.name: alarmText
alarmText.description: This describes the alarm generating the trap.

probableCause.name: probableCause
probableCause.description: This identifies the probable cause of the trap.

correctiveAction.name: correctiveAction
correctiveAction.description: This describes the actions to apply for correcting the problem that generated this alarm.

htimeStamp.name: htimeStamp
htimeStamp.description: Time-Stamp recorded in the log generated by this alarm.
